programme.desc: Zhengde flees the palace after his mother orders him to marry an ugly princess. He disguises as a commoner and escapes with his advisors, but a gambling mishap causes them to part ways.

programme.title: Midnight Diner
programme.desc: A small restaurant in Shanghai is open only from midnight to early morning. Through the years, people come here to share their stories, taste the chef's delicious food and leave feeling comforted and fulfilled.

programme.title: Death Notice
programme.desc: A serial killer leaves death notices in a city, stating when, how and who he will murder. While the police sets up a special task force in response, they expose an even bigger conspiracy behind.

programme.title: My Prince Edward
programme.desc: A newly engaged Hong Kong woman tries to rid herself of a secret sham marriage to a mainlander that she was paid for years ago, before she can get married for real.

programme.title: Wolf Pack
programme.desc: The Wolf Pack which is led by Lao Diao discovers that a terrorist force is planning to destroy the China's energy source. Lao Diao is now entrusted with the task of leading his squad to fight back.

programme.title: Mr. McDreamy
programme.desc: An affluent second generation rich man squanders his parents' money and calls himself Mr McDreamy. When his parents finally had enough of him and disowned him, he decides to establish a 'Mr McDreamy Training Academy'.

programme.title: Voyage Of Emperor Chien Lung
programme.desc: Emperor Chien Lung continues his incognito voyage to southern China. Accompanied by the minister and the imperial scholar, they have many amusing encounters in Yangzhou.

programme.title: All Men Are Brothers
programme.desc: The patriotic story of seven warriors in the band of 108 outlaws at Mount Liang. The magnificent seven battle against the despotic government officials to save their country.

programme.title: The Duel
programme.desc: After knowing his brother has killed the head of a rival triad, Jie takes the blame and was hunted by killers. With the help of Rambler Nan, Jie finally killed his enemies, but then found out that Nan is the one who has killed his father.

programme.title: The Big Sting
programme.desc: Three buddies find a rare artifact known as the Double-Faced God but are poisoned by Lady Wu who steals the treasure from them. Before they die, they get their wives to promise to train their children to take it back.

programme.title: The Deadly Breaking Sword
programme.desc: Warrior Tuan Chang Qing meets courtesan Liu Yin Xi in a small town. Liu pleads Tuan to kill the underworld master Guo Tian Sheng, known as the 'Killer Doctor', in order to avenge the death of her fiance.

programme.title: We Love Millionaires
programme.desc: Three beautiful Hong Kong salesgirls journey north to masquerade as high society debutantes and make their dreams of a gold-plated walk down the aisle come true.

programme.title: The Battle Wizard
programme.desc: Dali Prince Tuan Yu knows nothing about martial arts, but leaves the palace for the martial arts world. He meets a snake sorceress and his mysterious half-sister.

programme.title: Princess Iron Fan
programme.desc: The Monkey King and his gang are confronted by the evil Princess Iron Fan, Madam White Bone and her two sexy sisters, plus a cast of fanciful characters.

programme.title: The Black Lizard
programme.desc: Young swordsman Lung Fei encounters strange omens portending the death of his fiance. His enquiries with the help of Chief Constable Tieh Hu reveal an astounding story.

programme.title: Dawn Will Come
programme.desc: Liang Cai drugged the beautiful Qiu Rong and raped her, but promised to marry her after getting his parent's consent. Since then, there is no news of his proposal and she confronts him when she finds herself pregnant.

programme.title: Twin Blades Of Doom
programme.desc: A retired martial artist is forced back into action after his family is murdered by the evil Ghost Gang. Without friends, he is forced to ally himself with a quintet of killers.

programme.title: Forever Diamonds
programme.desc: Hua, a pretty fraud, steals a brilliant diamond ring from a shop in Hong Kong and escapes to Singapore. To smuggle the ring pass customs, Hua slips it into the pocket of a stranger, Yen, but then lost track of him.

programme.title: The Lady Professional
programme.desc: Lily Ho stars as a seductive hit woman in this contemporary Shaw Bros action thriller. Filmed in HK and Japan the story follows Ho's assassin as she discovers she is now a target.

programme.title: Raw Passions
programme.desc: A dedicated wife uncovers a web of blackmail and deceit after her husband is conned by a conniving belly dancer. When the dancer is stabbed, things quickly go from bad to insane.

programme.title: The Magnificent Swordsman
programme.desc: The Magnificent Swordsman centers on the hero vowing vengeance against evil bandits that killed his family when he was a child.

programme.title: Swordsman At Large
programme.desc: Bandits, beauties, and blade masters battle for survival in this exciting story of deceit, betrayal, and death.

programme.title: The Shadow Boxer
programme.desc: Skilled shadow Tai Chi boxer Ku Ting hides his skills by working as a construction worker. However, when the thugs assaulted his girlfriend, Ku Ting has no choice but to use his kung fu to beat his enemies.

programme.title: The Condemned
programme.desc: David Chiang plays a righteous character who helps an unjustly imprisoned swordsman accused of stealing. Together they break out of prison and serve notice to all the evil men that a new deadly duo is in town.

programme.title: Gossip Street
programme.desc: Shaw Bros and TVB stars unite for Wang Feng's ensemble epic. Trouble is brewing when a gangster plans to change the Gossip Street residents' favourite hangout into a gambling den.

programme.title: Shaolin Prince
programme.desc: When the Emperor is killed and the throne is usurped by Lord 9, his two baby princes are entrusted to the care of three Shaolin monks and the premier.

programme.title: Crazy Shaolin Disciples
programme.desc: Three young kung-fu warriors from wildly different backgrounds: Royal Guard Lo Lieh, fleeing soldier Lo Meng, and villager Wang Yu become students of Shaolin at the same temple.

programme.title: Brave Archer And His Mate
programme.desc: Guo Jing and Huang Rong raise the son of his sworn brother Yang Kang and named him Yang Guo. To prevent Yang Guo from taking revenge for his father's death, Huang Rong bans him from learning martial arts.

programme.title: Les Belles
programme.desc: Linda Lin Dai and Fanny Fan join the dancing troupe of Kao Pao-shu. Linda and Kao's son Peter Chen, manager of the troupe, have misunderstandings and dislike each other.

programme.title: The Thundering Sword
programme.desc: When Grand Master's student Yu falls for Chiao Chiao, the daughter of his arch enemy, they are in for trouble. This is made worse when Chiao Chiao kills a clansman in Yu's name.

programme.title: The Three Smiles
programme.desc: A talented scholar, Bo Hu, is attracted by the pretty maid, Qiu Xiang. In order to get close to her and win her love, he disguises as a servant to work in the same household.

programme.title: The Flying Dagger
programme.desc: The Yu family and the Green Dragon clan became enemies when the Yu daughter killed the clan head's son, who was a rapist and murderer. The Green Dragon leader wounds the head of the Yu family with his flying daggers.

programme.title: Rose, Be My Love
programme.desc: Set on the eve of the Japanese invasion of HK, this tragic Shaw Brothers romance stars Li Ting and Kwan Shan as young lovers torn apart by war.

programme.title: The Brave Archer
programme.desc: Guo Jing meets Huang Rong and they quickly fall in love. However, Ouyang Ke proposes to marry Huang Rong at the same time, so Huang's father sets up a duel for the two men to compete for her hand.

programme.title: The Happy Trio
programme.desc: Li Ching, the best actress of her era, play Ah Chiao is a girl from a rural village stranded in the city, who befriends a kind-hearted transient and a retired actor.

programme.title: My Dream Boat
programme.desc: This is a story about the complicated love relationships between a group of young friends who are entangled in a web of love and emotions.

programme.title: Call Of The Sea
programme.desc: A young fisherman, Chin Hu is in love with his childhood friend Hsiao Yu. However, the only son of a town bully lusts after Hsiao Yu's beauty and tries all possible ways to approach her.

programme.title: 7-Man Army
programme.desc: In 1933, 20,000 Japanese soldiers and 50 tanks strategically invaded the Great Wall.

programme.title: Young Lovers
programme.desc: Guitar-playing rich kid, Yang Fan, heads to Japan to join a rock 'n' roll band where he soon finds himself competing for the affections of two beautiful girls.

programme.title: Long Road To Gallantry
programme.desc: Roving swordsman Tu Meng-Fei chances to rescue a female pupil Mu Wan-Erh and later, another girl Li Sai-Nan from underworld leader Leng Tien-Lei. Li wants to take vengeance on Leng who murdered her parents.

programme.title: Love Parade
programme.desc: Fashion designer Shi asks his friend Mui to comment on his new design but is angered by her criticism. She asks him to design a gown for her to attend a gala event, Shi takes revenge by making a clown costume instead.

programme.title: Five Tough Guys
programme.desc: A titular gang of misfits come together to protect a patriotic general from a scheming usurper. To this end, the unlikely heroes act as the general's escorts on a dangerous journey to a distant British consulate.

programme.title: The Love Eterne
programme.desc: The glorious Betty Loh Ti stars as a beauty who disguises herself as a boy in order to receive a forbidden education in this multi award-winning drama from director Li Han Hsiang.

programme.title: The Singing Killer
programme.desc: Chiang Yi is blackmailed into a jewellery heist by his former boss, who threatens to expose his shady past. Complications arise when he discovers his first love works at the store.

programme.title: Love Without End
programme.desc: Singer Qing Qing and architect Tang Peng Nan are a sweet couple. She sacrifices herself to help Peng Nan at a time when his family is going through difficulties and is misunderstood by him, leading to their break up.

programme.title: Village Of Tigers
programme.desc: The devilish residents of the Village of Tigers, led by Hu Jiao, plan to kill Lo Hong Shun, otherwise known as the heroic Sword of the Southern Sky.

programme.title: The Comedy Of Mismatches
programme.desc: Two pairs of lovers got mismatched accidentally. The man disguises as a woman for his sister's wedding ceremony, while his lover disguises as a man to marry another woman.

programme.title: The Tigress Of Shaolin
programme.desc: Sam is being hunted as he discovers that the mayor and the chief of medical bureau are colluding with a drug dealer. He escapes to Shaolin to learn the cudgel style of kung fu in order to avenge his friends.

programme.title: Hell Has No Boundary
programme.desc: After suffering an out-of-the-blue seizure during a camping trip, female police officer May returns to active duty, only for bizarre happenings and death to follow her around.

programme.title: Pursuit Of Vengeance
programme.desc: Kung Fu legend Ti Lung stars in the action movie as Fu Xue Hong, embarking on a epic journey of revenge for his father.

programme.title: The Lady Assassin
programme.desc: Two feuding princes fight for the throne in the Qing Dynasty. Can the lady assassin who is drawn into this royal feud execute her assassination mission in time to help one of the princes secure the throne?

programme.title: The Female Prince
programme.desc: Ching Feng-Hsiao disguises herself as male to enroll for the imperial examination in order to save her lover from being framed by her stepmother. Can she make it?

programme.title: Pursuit Of A Killer
programme.desc: Lo Meng plays a Mainland Chinese criminal escapee to Hong Kong in search of a better life, and a cop helps him adjust to Hong Kong life while tracking down his mysterious killer at the same time.

programme.title: The Lark
programme.desc: Sixties popstar Carrie Ku Mei plays the 'Little Lark' in this frothy romance of mistaken identity that is a treasure trove of some of the most popular Mandarin songs of all time.

programme.title: The Eunuch
programme.desc: Before directing Bruce Lee in Fist Of Fury, Lo Wei wrote and starred in this story of a treacherous devil who will happily murder the Emperor to secure ultimate power for himself.

programme.title: Puppy Love
programme.desc: This is a story of adolescent playfulness and innocence lost. Two best friends grow up together, but rivalry intervenes when they discover boys!

programme.title: Rolls, Rolls, I Love You
programme.desc: Three young men offend a billionaire and are drawn into a high stakes bet. If they win, they get to keep the billionaire's Rolls Royce. Otherwise, they will need to pay the rich man fifty thousand dollars!

programme.title: Return Of The Crazy Bumpkins
programme.desc: Sequel to the John Lo Mar/Chang Yang original finds immigrant Yeh Feng leaving jail to live with crooked uncle Wang Sha, but his girlfriend Ai Ti has married an abusive husband.

programme.title: Trilogy Of Swordsmanship
programme.desc: A kung fu anthology film consisting of three stories: a man embarrasses himself, a courtesan in love with a general and a group of bandits forms a plan to rescue a new friend from being executed.

programme.title: Passing Flickers
programme.desc: An amusing insider's look at the Hong Kong film industry from Li Han Hsiang, recreating some of the era's funniest and most surreal stories ripped straight from the gossip.

programme.title: Six Assassins
programme.desc: Lord Li Ming is a feudal tyrant who oppresses the people, and even the Emperor who is his brother, cannot stop his evil act. Righteous swordsman Mu poses as Li Ming's guard to plan for his assassination.
